{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VL9DoSBWPnWENYV4xMAtcX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent\n     2→\n     3→Every time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n     4→\n     5→## Why?\n     6→\n     7→Standard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n     8→\n     9→- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n    10→- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n    11→- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n    12→- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n    13→\n    14→## Available Agents\n    15→\n    16→| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n    17→|-------|-----------|-------|\n    18→| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n    19→| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n    20→| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n    21→| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n    22→| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n    23→\n    24→## Quick Start\n    25→\n    26→### Install via curl\n    27→\n    28→```sh\n    29→curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→### Install from local clone\n    33→\n    34→```sh\n    35→git clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\n    36→cd x-agent\n    37→sh install.sh\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→Local installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\n    41→The installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\n    42→It also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n    43→\n    44→### Use directly (no install)\n    45→\n    46→```sh\n    47→# Rust project\n    48→path/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n    49→\n    50→# Node.js project\n    51→path/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n    52→\n    53→# Python project\n    54→path/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n    55→\n    56→# Terraform project\n    57→path/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→## Usage\n    61→\n    62→### bash-agent\n    63→\n    64→```sh\n    65→bash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\n    66→bash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\n    67→bash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\n    68→SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n    69→```\n    70→\n    71→### cargo-agent\n    72→\n    73→```sh\n    74→cargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\n    75→cargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\n    76→cargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\n    77→cargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\n    78→cargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n    79→```\n    80→\n    81→### npm-agent\n    82→\n    83→```sh\n    84→npm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\n    85→npm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n    86→npm-agent.sh test           # tests only\n    87→npm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→npm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n    91→\n    92→### py-agent\n    93→\n    94→```sh\n    95→py-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\n    96→py-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\n    97→py-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n    98→py-agent.sh test           # tests only\n    99→py-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n   100→```\n   101→\n   102→py-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n   103→\n   104→### terra-agent\n   105→\n   106→```sh\n   107→terra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\n   108→terra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\n   109→terra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\n   110→terra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\n   111→terra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\n   112→TERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\n   113→FMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n   114→```\n   115→\n   116→`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n   117→`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n   118→\n   119→## Environment Knobs\n   120→\n   121→All agents share the same pattern:\n   122→\n   123→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   124→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   125→| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n   126→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n   127→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n   128→\n   129→```sh\n   130→# Skip tests, keep logs\n   131→RUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n   132→\n   133→# Only run lint and typecheck\n   134→RUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→## Output Format\n   138→\n   139→```\n   140→------------------------------------------------------------\n   141→Step: clippy\n   142→Errors: 0\n   143→Warnings: 3\n   144→\n   145→Diagnostics (first 40 lines):\n   146→warning: unused variable `x`\n   147→warning: unused import `std::io`\n   148→warning: function `old_handler` is never used\n   149→\n   150→Result: PASS\n   151→Full JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\n   152→Lean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\n   153→Time: 4s\n   154→------------------------------------------------------------\n   155→Overall: PASS\n   156→Logs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n   157→```\n   158→\n   159→On **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n   160→\n   161→## Claude Code Skills\n   162→\n   163→The `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n   164→\n   165→- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n   166→- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n   167→- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n   168→- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n   169→- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n   170→\n   171→## License\n   172→\n   173→MIT\n   174→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d69c5f-0ac2-4adc-92c8-852dd8c9cd25","uuid":"3f429413-5d5c-4c2c-896a-3cd54c2e2c1a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md","content":"# x-agent\n\nEvery time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n\n## Why?\n\nStandard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n\n- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n\n## Available Agents\n\n| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n|-------|-----------|-------|\n| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Install via curl\n\n```sh\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n### Install from local clone\n\n```sh\ngit clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\ncd x-agent\nsh install.sh\n```\n\nLocal installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\nThe installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\nIt also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n\n### Use directly (no install)\n\n```sh\n# Rust project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Node.js project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n\n# Python project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n\n# Terraform project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### bash-agent\n\n```sh\nbash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\nbash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\nbash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\nSHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n```\n\n### cargo-agent\n\n```sh\ncargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\ncargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\ncargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\ncargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\ncargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n```\n\n### npm-agent\n\n```sh\nnpm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\nnpm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\nnpm-agent.sh test           # tests only\nnpm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n```\n\nnpm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n\n### py-agent\n\n```sh\npy-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\npy-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\npy-agent.sh lint           # lint only\npy-agent.sh test           # tests only\npy-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n```\n\npy-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n\n### terra-agent\n\n```sh\nterra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\nterra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\nterra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\nterra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\nterra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\nTERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\nFMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n```\n\n`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n\n## Environment Knobs\n\nAll agents share the same pattern:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n\n```sh\n# Skip tests, keep logs\nRUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Only run lint and typecheck\nRUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\n```\n------------------------------------------------------------\nStep: clippy\nErrors: 0\nWarnings: 3\n\nDiagnostics (first 40 lines):\nwarning: unused variable `x`\nwarning: unused import `std::io`\nwarning: function `old_handler` is never used\n\nResult: PASS\nFull JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\nLean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\nTime: 4s\n------------------------------------------------------------\nOverall: PASS\nLogs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n```\n\nOn **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n\n## Claude Code Skills\n\nThe `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n\n- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":174,"startLine":1,"totalLines":174}}}
