lude `go-agent` in skill selection, dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet.\n- [x] 12. Update `README.md` to list go-agent in Available Agents and add usage examples.\n- [x] 13. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema\n- [x] 14. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS","originalFile":"## Implementation Checklist\n- [ ] 1. Confirm go-agent scope and current runner contract by reviewing `.ralph/task.md`, `.ralph/specs/04-go-agent.md`, `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`, and existing shared-lib patterns.\n- [ ] 2. Create `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh` with shared-lib sourcing (`lib/x-agent-common.sh`) and domain-step execution only.\n- [ ] 3. Implement universal and go-specific knobs in `go-agent.sh` with safe defaults and CI-aware `FMT_MODE` behavior (`auto` => CI check, local fix).\n- [ ] 4. Implement `run_fmt` using `gofmt -l` in check mode and `gofmt -w` in fix mode, including structured result/fix hints and CHANGED_FILES scoped targets.\n- [ ] 5. Implement `run_vet` with `go vet` and `staticcheck` detection wrapper, keeping `staticcheck` optional with required skip message and scoped/unscope package execution.\n- [ ] 6. Implement `run_test` using `go test` with failing test extraction from `--- FAIL:` lines and rich `Fix:` hint.\n- [ ] 7. Implement robust CHANGED_FILES-to-package mapping for Go fixtures and package args for `go vet`, `staticcheck`, and `go test`.\n- [ ] 8. Add command dispatch (`fmt`, `vet`, `staticcheck`, `test`, `all`, plus `--fail-fast`, `help`/`-h` before need()) and final `Overall` flow with `overall_ok` accumulation.\n- [ ] 9. Create `skills/go-agent/SKILL.md` with trigger text and allowed-tools including `FMT_MODE=*` and CHANGED_FILES.\n- [ ] 10. Add `tests/go-agent/clean/scenario.env` and `tests/go-agent/issues/scenario.env` with required fixtures (`go.mod`, `main.go`) and `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"go\"`.\n- [ ] 11. Update `install.sh` to include `go-agent` in skill selection, dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet.\n- [ ] 12. Update `README.md` to list go-agent in Available Agents and add usage examples.\n- [ ] 13. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema\n- [ ] 14. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS\n\n## Architecture Review\n\n### System Design and Boundaries\n\nThe go-agent should follow the existing architecture layering:\n\n- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: domain-specific command runner only.\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime helpers (outdir lifecycle, locking, formatting utilities, fail-fast flow, tool check).\n- `tests/go-agent/*`: fixture contracts validated by `tests/run-scenarios.sh`.\n- `install.sh` + `README.md`: packaging and discoverability boundary.\n\nPrimary coupling points:\n\n- Script-to-lib path coupling via `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib`.\n- External tool contracts to `go`, `gofmt`, `go vet`, and optionally `staticcheck`.\n- Fixture contract coupling to `tests/run-scenarios.sh` (`scenario.env` fields and `EXPECT_EXIT`).\n\n### Dependency Graph and Coupling Risks\n\n- Mandatory runtime path: command script → source helper lib → invoke domain steps.\n- High-coupling risk: all helpers are assumed to exist in `x-agent-common.sh`; any API change there affects all agents.\n- Command coupling risk: `run_scenarios` can execute `go-agent` by path from `AGENT_SCRIPT`; install path integrity must hold.\n- Data coupling risk: lockfile filename string in `setup_lock` is based on agent name, so using a wrong name breaks lock isolation.\n\n### Data Flow and Bottlenecks\n\nFlow:\n\n1. Parse args, handle help/fail-fast.\n2. Validate required tool (`go`), initialize outdir + lock.\n3. Resolve `CHANGED_FILES` → package scope list.\n4. Run selected steps in `all` with `should_continue`.\n5. Write complete step logs to `$OUTDIR`, print truncated output and status.\n6. Return PASS/FAIL summary.\n\nPotential bottlenecks:\n\n- `go vet`/`go test`/`go list` are the dominant costs; all else is O(n) path preprocessing.\n- Staticcheck path is optional, so if installed it adds another full traversal.\n\n### Security Architecture\n\n- No new service/auth boundaries; only local filesystem and shell tool invocation.\n- Inputs are env+args; command construction should avoid indirect eval-like behavior.\n- Existing shell risk pattern (trusted project-local files and variables) remains; maintain existing conventions.\n- Lock files are advisory; avoid predictable collisions outside agent namespace.\n\n### Architectural Options and Tradeoffs\n\n1) CHANGED_FILES package scoping strategy\n- Option A: Direct directory derivation (`dirname` on changed `.go` files).\n  - Effort: low, deterministic.\n  - Risk: may include non-package directories; tool calls may produce extra work.\n  - Impact: simple and fast.\n- Option B: Resolve each changed directory with `go list` validation.\n  - Effort: medium.\n  - Risk: introduces extra command invocations.\n  - Impact: more precise package targeting.\n- Option C: Ignore CHANGED_FILES and always run on `./...`.\n  - Effort: lowest.\n  - Risk: slow and noisy; violates FR-3 requirement.\n\nRecommendation: Option A with minimal `go list`-style fallback where needed. Keeps runtime low and satisfies FR scope behavior.\n\n2) Fail hint construction\n- Option A: Generic hints only.\n  - Effort: low.\n  - Risk: misses required `TestFoo` extraction detail.\n- Option B: Parse `go test` output for named fails and join names in hint.\n  - Effort: moderate string parsing.\n  - Risk: brittle output variations; manageable with grep/sed patterns.\n  - Impact: higher value diagnostics.\n\nRecommendation: Option B (required by FR-12). Keep fallback generic if parsing fails.\n\n3) CI format behavior\n- Option A: Respect only user `FMT_MODE`.\n  - Risk: conflicts with FR-10.\n- Option B: `if CI` force check regardless of env.\n  - Effort: minimal.\n  - Impact: deterministic behavior and CI parity.\n\nRecommendation: Option B.\n\n### Implications for Future Specs\n\n- This agent cements go-scoping helper expectations before US-05..10 start.\n- If CHANGED_FILES resolution grows complex (e.g., vendor/module roots), consider adding a reusable helper in shared lib in a later spec.\n- Ensure future agents that map changed files to target packages use similar scoped arg strategy for consistency.\n\n## Code Quality Planning\n\n### Module Structure and Organization\n\n- Keep `go-agent.sh` under ~200 lines of domain logic by using shared lib helpers.\n- Separate concerns by function:\n  - env/usage\n  - scope resolution\n  - one `run_<step>` per command\n  - `main()` dispatcher\n\n### DRY and Duplication\n\n- Reuse common output helpers (`step`, `fmt_elapsed`, `print_overall`, `print_result`, `setup_*`, `need`, `should_continue`).\n- Avoid duplicating lock/setup/cleanup blocks.\n- Build a single scoped target helper used by `fmt`, `vet`, `staticcheck`, and `test`.\n- Shared log names by step: `<step>.log`.\n\n### Explicit Error Handling (all edge cases)\n\n- Missing required `go`: fail fast via `need go` with exit `2`.\n- Missing optional `staticcheck`: report `SKIP` and continue.\n- Missing `.go` files and/or no valid scoped dirs:\n  - `fmt`: fallback to `.` in local/full mode.\n  - vet/test/staticcheck: fallback to `./...` for safety.\n- Command failures:\n  - emit `Result: FAIL` and `Fix:` line with actionable command.\n  - preserve full output under `$OUTDIR`.\n- Empty fixtures/parse failures:\n  - treat as non-fatal unless command output indicates actionable error.\n- `help` invocation should bypass project/tool validation.\n\n### Technical Debt Prevention\n\n- Keep argument forwarding minimal and explicit to avoid shell injection and accidental argument loss.\n- Preserve output contract (`Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix`, `Time`, `Overall`, `Logs`) and exit semantics.\n- Use stable helper calls instead of hand-rolled traps/lock logic.\n- Keep CHANGED_FILES parsing intentionally simple and documented to match existing repo conventions unless future spec explicitly lifts the space-in-filename limitation.\n\n### Engineering Level\n\n- Implement the smallest robust solution that meets FRs, avoid over-generalizing scoping beyond required `.go` behavior.\n- Prefer readable Bash 3.2-compatible logic over compact but opaque string pipelines.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit/Function-level\n\nBecause this repo is shell-driven, tests are primarily scenario-based, but internal behavior should still be validated by execution behavior:\n\n- Run help path with no tools/project context to assert pre-tool usage handling.\n- Simulate `CHANGED_FILES` with known `.go` file lists and verify scope output (when non-empty).\n- Ensure `FMT_MODE=check` and `FMT_MODE=fix` are honored and that CI mode forces check.\n\n### Integration (Scenario Tests)\n\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh go-agent` (must report no failures):\n  - clean expects PASS\n  - issues expects FAIL\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh shellcheck` (indirectly covered by full run) after script creation.\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`.\n- Manual execution inside fixture dirs:\n  - `FMT_MODE=check` on clean and issue scenarios.\n  - `FMT_MODE=fix` on issue scenario to validate rewrite and non-failing return (where fixture is only formatting issue).\n  - `RUN_STATICCHECK=0` to verify command-level toggle behavior.\n\n### Failure Modes and Edge Cases in Tests\n\n- `go` missing in environment: scenario marked SKIP via REQUIRED_TOOLS in fixture.\n- `staticcheck` missing: step must return SKIP and `all` continues to remaining steps.\n- `CHANGED_FILES` with only non-`.go` entries: should degrade to unscoped package-level behavior.\n- `RUN_*` toggles set to `0` skip intended steps.\n- `--fail-fast=1` in all mode halts after first failure, and `overall_ok` is returned correctly.\n\n### Assertion Strength\n\n- Validate exit codes exactly (`EXPECT_EXIT`) through scenario harness.\n- Validate each step’s status string (`Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`) and presence of `Fix:` on failures.\n- Validate failure hints contain either actionable test names or explicit staticcheck skip wording.\n- Validate logs are emitted and cleanup semantics follow `KEEP_DIR` and exit code.\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Query/Execution Patterns\n\n- Avoid running `go list ./...` multiple times in a single invocation when CHANGED_FILES is empty.\n- Reuse a single resolved scope list for vet/staticcheck/test; do not recompute per step.\n- Do not re-run `gofmt` on entire tree when scoped directories are known.\n\n### Memory/CPU\n\n- Keep process output on disk in per-step logs to avoid unbounded memory use.\n- Use lightweight text scans (`grep`/`sed`) only after commands fail.\n- Avoid storing huge package lists in command expansions where unnecessary.\n\n### Caching Opportunities\n\n- Cache scoped directory list once (environment variable/array) and reuse across steps.\n- Reuse the same scope when command arguments are unchanged.\n\n### Slow Paths\n\n- `go test` and `go vet` are inherently expensive; scope reduction via CHANGED_FILES is the main optimization.\n- staticcheck adds additional CPU; skip when unavailable.\n\n## Decision Log\n\n### Decision 1: Script source path strategy\n- Alternatives:\n  - A) Use `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib/x-agent-common.sh` (same as existing agents).\n  - B) Add lib path resolver utility in common layer.\n  - C) Use env override for lib path.\n- Chosen: A.\n- Why: explicit requirement alignment and lowest churn; predictable for this spec.\n- Implications: keep in sync with existing install/local path assumptions.\n\n### Decision 2: Scope target derivation for changed files\n- Alternatives:\n  - A) Use file-directory projection only.\n  - B) Resolve each directory through `go list`.\n  - C) Ignore CHANGED_FILES.\n- Chosen: A with safe fallback to full run.\n- Why: meets FR while keeping runtime low and implementation compact.\n- Implications: behavior remains intuitive and fast; future helper extraction can refine precision.\n\n### Decision 3: Test failure hint extraction\n- Alternatives:\n  - A) Generic failure message.\n  - B) Parse `--- FAIL:` and include test list.\n  - C) Parse package-wide summary lines.\n- Chosen: B.\n- Why: directly satisfies FR-12 and improves remediation speed.\n- Implications: depends on go test output format; add fallback generic hint if parse misses.\n\n### Decision 4: Install/README updates\n- Alternatives:\n  - A) Delay and only rely on hidden agent selection.\n  - B) Register in `install.sh` and docs immediately.\n- Chosen: B.\n- Why: aligns with project standards and user discoverability requirements.\n- Implications: no discoverability gap when agent is added.\n\n## Edge Cases and Risks\n\n- `CHANGED_FILES` containing spaces: consistent with current project convention, this splits on spaces and may mis-handle such paths.\n- `gofmt -l` returns non-zero only on parse errors; must use output emptiness as pass/fail in check mode.\n- Staticcheck skip path must not abort agent execution.\n- go test can return fail with output in stderr only; capture both streams consistently.\n- `--fail-fast` with `all` and scoped steps must preserve `overall_ok` and return code semantics.\n- `go test` failures can include package-level `FAIL` banners without any `--- FAIL:` lines; still provide generic fix hint.\n- `all` mode under `KEEP_DIR=0` must preserve logs only on failure.\n- `FMT_MODE=auto` plus explicit `FMT_MODE=fix/check` in environment should have deterministic priority.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n1. What: Add the new script skeleton and shared-lib integration.\n   Why: Aligns with architecture and keeps script length under target threshold.\n   How: copy style from `skills/py-agent`/`skills/terra-agent` with `set -euo pipefail`, doc header, source block, usage, dispatcher.\n   Edge cases: help path must run before `need go`; lock setup should happen only for real command runs.\n   Tests: `bash -n skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`.\n   Risks: missing source order breaking `shellcheck` directives.\n\n2. What: Implement universal and agent knobs including `FMT_MODE` normalization.\n   Why: ensures local vs CI behavior and user control for each step.\n   How: define `RUN_FMT`, `RUN_VET`, `RUN_STATICCHECK`, `RUN_TESTS`, `FMT_MODE`, then normalize mode in run-time block:\n   - `FMT_MODE=auto`: local fix, CI check\n   - explicit `check|fix`: preserved unless CI then forced check.\n   Edge cases: invalid `FMT_MODE` values should fail with clear message and exit 2.\n   Tests: `go-agent fmt` with `FMT_MODE=check/fix/auto` and simulated `CI=true`.\n   Risks: accidental local mutation in CI due mode override bug.\n\n3. What: Implement CHANGED_FILES resolver for Go package directories.\n   Why: supports FR-3 and performance optimization.\n   How: filter `CHANGED_FILES` for existing `.go` files, derive unique directories, print scope summary, and reuse same list across scoped steps.\n   Edge cases: missing file paths, duplicate dirs, non-package directories.\n   Tests: fixture run with `CHANGED_FILES` set to one file and multiple files.\n   Risks: over-broad dirs including nested non-package parents.\n\n4. What: Implement `run_fmt` with scoped check/fix semantics.\n   Why: FR-7/FR-10 requirement, biggest local improvement path.\n   How: in check mode, run `gofmt -l` against targets, fail when output non-empty; in fix mode, run `gofmt -w`, pass on formatting success.\n   Edge cases: check mode output can include many lines; output summary plus truncated snippet.\n   Tests: clean fixture pass, issue fixture fail in check, fix succeed in fix mode.\n   Risks: false fail when command exits 0 despite unchanged files.\n\n5. What: Implement `run_vet` with stdout/stderr-aware logging and fail hint.\n   Why: FR for vet diagnostics and actionable fix path.\n   How: run `go vet` with scoped args/default `./...`, capture output to `$OUTDIR/vet.log`; print tail on failure and `Fix:` hint.\n   Edge cases: `go vet` writes to stderr; ensure both streams captured.\n   Tests: issue fixture vet failure with `go test` pass, and clean fixture pass.\n   Risks: noisy output in large projects without truncation control.\n\n6. What: Implement optional `run_staticcheck` with skip-first behavior.\n   Why: FR-6 requires optional dependency handling.\n   How: check `command -v staticcheck`; if missing print exact SKIP message; else run with scoped args and same result semantics as other steps.\n   Edge cases: staticcheck exists but fails for malformed modules.\n   Tests: run with `RUN_STATICCHECK=1` in clean fixture and issue fixture; validate skip string when absent.\n   Risks: accidentally returning failure for missing optional tool.\n\n7. What: Implement `run_test` with failing-test extraction and hint formatting.\n   Why: direct FR requirement to list failing tests for fix hint.\n   How: run `go test` to log file, parse lines matching `^--- FAIL:` and extract test names; dedupe and join with `, `.\n   Edge cases: go test output formats can vary across subtest naming; fallback to generic hint.\n   Tests: create a failing test case if needed for deterministic extraction validation.\n   Risks: parser fragility in uncommon go versions.\n\n8. What: Implement command dispatch and all-mode orchestration.\n   Why: consistent user interface and expected control-flow.\n   How: support `fmt`, `vet`, `staticcheck`, `test`, `all`; parse `--fail-fast` and help options; guard each step with `RUN_*` and `should_continue`.\n   Edge cases: unknown command returns usage and exit code 2.\n   Tests: `go-agent`, `go-agent help`, `go-agent all`, invalid command.\n   Risks: argument parsing collisions when future subcommands expand.\n\n9. What: Add `skills/go-agent/SKILL.md` metadata and trigger coverage.\n   Why: necessary for agent invocation and allowed-tools discovery.\n   How: mirror style of existing agents; include `go agent`, `run go checks`, `golang checks`, etc.\n   Edge cases: missed `FMT_MODE=*` pattern blocks automation.\n   Tests: manual skill-readability validation.\n   Risks: inconsistent examples creating confusion for callers.\n\n10. What: Add fixtures for clean and issues scenarios and scenario env contracts.\n    Why: required harness coverage and behavior isolation.\n    How: create `tests/go-agent/clean` with `go.mod` + valid formatted `main.go`; create `tests/go-agent/issues` with `go.mod` + vet-triggering or formatting-bad `main.go`.\n    Edge cases: avoid adding dependencies beyond stdlib; keep fixture runtime fast.\n    Tests: `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"go\"` in both `scenario.env` files.\n    Risks: brittle fixture if go toolchain differences alter behavior.\n\n11. What: Update `install.sh` for discoverability and dependency checks.\n    Why: all new agents must be installable from supported toolchain path.\n    How: add `go-agent` to `SKILLS`, optional dependency check section, and AGENTS snippet output.\n    Edge cases: remote/local install behavior for script path patching.\n    Tests: `sh install.sh --help` and selected install flow with `go-agent`.\n    Risks: patch mismatch causing missing lib path for go-agent install.\n\n12. What: Update `README.md` documentation.\n    Why: maintain docs/usage parity and quick-start discoverability.\n    How: add row in Available Agents, `go-agent` usage examples and command samples.\n    Edge cases: keep language consistent with existing style.\n    Tests: visual/manual doc consistency check.\n    Risks: documentation drift from actual output contract.\n\n13. What: Update `.ralph/exploration.md` only if implementation changes documented boundaries/files/patterns.\n    Why: avoids repeated rediscovery for future specs.\n    How: keep entries concise and version-stable.\n    Edge cases: avoid stale references to planned/not-yet-existing files.\n    Tests: none (documentation review).\n    Risks: stale guidance if not updated before validation.\n\n14. What: Run final validation gates and close the plan.\n    Why: explicit acceptance requirement for this phase.\n    How: run `shellcheck`, `tests/run-scenarios.sh go-agent`, and `ralph validate work`.\n    Edge cases: validation failures must be corrected before moving to work phase.\n    Tests: record failures + fix plan.\n    Risks: tooling drift or missing go toolchain in environment causing false negatives.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":18,"newStart":1,"newLines":18,"lines":[" ## Implementation Checklist","-- [ ] 1. Confirm go-agent scope and current runner contract by reviewing `.ralph/task.md`, `.ralph/specs/04-go-agent.md`, `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`, and existing shared-lib patterns.","-- [ ] 2. Create `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh` with shared-lib sourcing (`lib/x-agent-common.sh`) and domain-step execution only.","-- [ ] 3. Implement universal and go-specific knobs in `go-agent.sh` with safe defaults and CI-aware `FMT_MODE` behavior (`auto` => CI check, local fix).","-- [ ] 4. Implement `run_fmt` using `gofmt -l` in check mode and `gofmt -w` in fix mode, including structured result/fix hints and CHANGED_FILES scoped targets.","-- [ ] 5. Implement `run_vet` with `go vet` and `staticcheck` detection wrapper, keeping `staticcheck` optional with required skip message and scoped/unscope package execution.","-- [ ] 6. Implement `run_test` using `go test` with failing test extraction from `--- FAIL:` lines and rich `Fix:` hint.","-- [ ] 7. Implement robust CHANGED_FILES-to-package mapping for Go fixtures and package args for `go vet`, `staticcheck`, and `go test`.","-- [ ] 8. Add command dispatch (`fmt`, `vet`, `staticcheck`, `test`, `all`, plus `--fail-fast`, `help`/`-h` before need()) and final `Overall` flow with `overall_ok` accumulation.","-- [ ] 9. Create `skills/go-agent/SKILL.md` with trigger text and allowed-tools including `FMT_MODE=*` and CHANGED_FILES.","-- [ ] 10. Add `tests/go-agent/clean/scenario.env` and `tests/go-agent/issues/scenario.env` with required fixtures (`go.mod`, `main.go`) and `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"go\"`.","-- [ ] 11. Update `install.sh` to include `go-agent` in skill selection, dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet.","-- [ ] 12. Update `README.md` to list go-agent in Available Agents and add usage examples.","-- [ ] 13. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema","-- [ ] 14. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS","+- [x] 1. Confirm go-agent scope and current runner contract by reviewing `.ralph/task.md`, `.ralph/specs/04-go-agent.md`, `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`, and existing shared-lib patterns.","+- [x] 2. Create `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh` with shared-lib sourcing (`lib/x-agent-common.sh`) and domain-step execution only.","+- [x] 3. Implement universal and go-specific knobs in `go-agent.sh` with safe defaults and CI-aware `FMT_MODE` behavior (`auto` => CI check, local fix).","+- [x] 4. Implement `run_fmt` using `gofmt -l` in check mode and `gofmt -w` in fix mode, including structured result/fix hints and CHANGED_FILES scoped targets.","+- [x] 5. Implement `run_vet` with `go vet` and `staticcheck` detection wrapper, keeping `staticcheck` optional with required skip message and scoped/unscope package execution.","+- [x] 6. Implement `run_test` using `go test` with failing test extraction from `--- FAIL:` lines and rich `Fix:` hint.","+- [x] 7. Implement robust CHANGED_FILES-to-package mapping for Go fixtures and package args for `go vet`, `staticcheck`, and `go test`.","+- [x] 8. Add command dispatch (`fmt`, `vet`, `staticcheck`, `test`, `all`, plus `--fail-fast`, `help`/`-h` before need()) and final `Overall` flow with `overall_ok` accumulation.","+- [x] 9. Create `skills/go-agent/SKILL.md` with trigger text and allowed-tools including `FMT_MODE=*` and CHANGED_FILES.","+- [x] 10. Add `tests/go-agent/clean/scenario.env` and `tests/go-agent/issues/scenario.env` with required fixtures (`go.mod`, `main.go`) and `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"go\"`.","+- [x] 11. Update `install.sh` to include `go-agent` in skill selection, dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet.","+- [x] 12. Update `README.md` to list go-agent in Available Agents and add usage examples.","+- [x] 13. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema","+- [x] 14. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS"," "," ## Architecture Review"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
