{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SjfcStFzKXd11cp4wzno1p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014RuBG1am92erWbSb13bFJf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt","content":"# Work Summary — Spec 04: go-agent\n\n## What was implemented\n\nCreated the go-agent — a lean Go workflow runner that checks formatting (gofmt), runs vet/lint (go vet, staticcheck), and executes tests (go test).\n\n### Files created:\n- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh` — main agent script (~230 lines total, ~170 lines domain code)\n- `skills/go-agent/SKILL.md` — trigger language, allowed-tools, and usage docs\n- `tests/go-agent/clean/scenario.env` + `go.mod` + `main.go` — passing fixture (valid formatted Go program)\n- `tests/go-agent/issues/scenario.env` + `go.mod` + `main.go` — failing fixture (`fmt.Printf(\"%d\", \"string\")` vet issue)\n\n### Files modified:\n- `install.sh` — added `go-agent` to SKILLS, go/staticcheck dep checks, and snippet line\n- `README.md` — added go-agent row in Available Agents table, usage section, direct-use example, and skill reference\n\n## Deviations from work plan\n\n- **No `setup_lock` call**: go-agent does not use workflow locking. `gofmt`, `go vet`, and `go test` are read-only or idempotent operations without shared state requiring serialization. This matches bash-agent, npm-agent, and terra-agent which also don't use locks.\n- **Issue fixture uses vet issue only** (not formatting): Using `fmt.Printf(\"%d\", \"string\")` which triggers `go vet` reliably. The code is already properly gofmt-formatted (gofmt doesn't care about semantic issues), so the failure comes from the vet step. This is more robust across Go versions than trying to create formatting issues.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- `CHANGED_FILES` filtering: only existing `.go` files are included, unique directories derived\n- `FMT_MODE=auto`: resolves to `fix` locally, `check` in CI; CI forces `check` regardless of explicit setting\n- Invalid `FMT_MODE` values: prints error and exits 2\n- Missing `staticcheck`: prints `Result: SKIP` with install instructions, continues to remaining steps\n- `gofmt -l` exit code handling: checks output emptiness (not exit code) since gofmt exits 0 even when files need formatting\n- Help/--help/-h: handled before `need` checks so it works without go installed\n- Unknown commands: print usage and exit 2\n- Test failure extraction: parses `--- FAIL:` lines from go test output; falls back to generic hint if none found\n- `FAIL_FAST`: uses `should_continue()` from shared lib in `all` command path\n\n## Tests written/run\n- `tests/go-agent/clean/` — passes with exit 0 (valid Go project, all checks pass)\n- `tests/go-agent/issues/` — fails with exit 1 (go vet catches Printf format mismatch)\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` passes on go-agent.sh itself\n- Full suite: all 16 scenarios pass (including all existing agents)\n\n## Known limitations\n- `CHANGED_FILES` splits on whitespace; paths with spaces are not supported (matches convention used by all other agents)\n- `gofmt` operates on directories rather than individual files when scoped; this may format unchanged files in the same directory\n- `staticcheck` is fully optional; if not installed, that analysis step is simply skipped\n\n## Feedback Closure Matrix\nNo prior review issues exist for this spec (first implementation).\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`: changed go-agent entries from \"to be added\" to actual descriptions of implemented files, noted the vet-based issue fixture strategy.\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\nNo prior lessons existed for this project. Followed established patterns from bash-agent implementation (print_result usage, help-before-need, issue fixture design).\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify `--help` works without go installed (help is parsed before `need go`)\n- The issue fixture relies on `go vet` detecting `Printf` format mismatch — confirm this triggers on the reviewer's Go version\n- `staticcheck` step correctly SKIPs when not installed (doesn't fail the run)\n- `FMT_MODE` CI override is tested implicitly through the clean fixture (which runs with default auto mode = fix locally)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":153,"cache_read_input_tokens":69414,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":153},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d69c5f-0ac2-4adc-92c8-852dd8c9cd25","uuid":"5bf3d34a-3934-4753-95c2-022f629b0967"}
